docs.abstract: The Trump administration has proposed reducing the number of prescription drugs that must be made available to people with cancer, AIDS, depression, schizophrenia and certain other conditions.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration has proposed reducing the number of prescription drugs that must be made available to people with cancer, AIDS, depression, schizophrenia and certain other conditions.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration proposed on Monday to cut costs for Medicare by reducing the number of prescription drugs that must be made available to people with cancer, AIDS, depression, schizophrenia and certain other conditions.

headline.main: Trump Moves to Lower Medicare Drug Costs by Relaxing Some Patient Protections
headline.print_headline: Trump Moves to Lower Drug Costs by Relaxing Some Protections for Patients

docs.abstract: The Trump administration is considering a legal definition of gender as immutable and fixed at birth, the most drastic in a series of moves against transgender people.
docs.snippet: The Trump administration is considering a legal definition of gender as immutable and fixed at birth, the most drastic in a series of moves against transgender people.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration is considering narrowly defining gender as a biological, immutable condition determined by genitalia at birth, the most drastic move yet in a governmentwide effort to roll back recognition and protections of transgender people under federal civil rights law.

headline.main: ‘Transgender’ Could Be Defined Out of Existence Under Trump Administration
headline.print_headline: Trump May Limit How Government Defines One’s Sex

docs.abstract: Women who are unable to obtain health insurance coverage for contraceptives through their employers could seek assistance at family planning clinics, the administration says.
docs.snippet: Women who are unable to obtain health insurance coverage for contraceptives through their employers could seek assistance at family planning clinics, the administration says.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration is making it easier for employers to exclude birth control from health insurance benefits provided under the Affordable Care Act, and it has come up with a new justification, saying that female employees can obtain contraceptives at family planning clinics for low-income people.

headline.main: Trump Proposes a New Way Around Birth Control Mandate: Religious Exemptions and Title X
